With the text of the subjoined inscription, I have compared four other inscriptions of
Rājendra-Choḷa, viz., 1. the inscription No. 68, which is likewise dated in the 12th year;
2. an undated inscription of the Kailāsanātha Temple at Uttaramallūr in the
Chingleput District, an impression of which I owe to the kindness of Mr. R.Sewell;
3. an inscription of the Br̥hadīśvara Temple at Tanjore (15th year); and 4. an
inscription of the Chidambaram Temple (24th year).

(Line 17.) The son of Mahendravarman, by whom prosperity was thoroughly
produced (su-rachita), just as prosperity is heaped on the gods (sura-chita) by Mahendra;
and who thoroughly enforced the sacred law of the castes and the orders;——
